<p><b>What is culture according to Kramsch?</b> Kramsch (1998) defined the concept of culture as "membership in a discourse community that shares a common social space and history, and common imaginings" (p. 10). ... ... Culture, in this sense, is the interaction or the product of interaction among three elements: people, places, and practices (actions).</p>
