<p><b>How does language reflect our culture?</b> Language is created and shaped by the needs of a culture as it changes. Language is more than words, and includes the way we speak in different accents and dialects. Language also includes coded cultural messages understood by those within a culture, but not necessarily by those outside it.</p>
