<p><b>What came first, language or culture?</b> From the start, human beings are communicating and interacting with each other in different ways. Thus, for obvious reasons, the language came first. Language is the source as well as the essence of a culture. With time, many languages evolved, and today, a large number of languages are spoken across the world.</p>
